refsect1.para:
  Mandatory arguments to long options are mandatory for short options too.


    &opt_h;
    &opt_help;



        display help message and terminate





    &opt_version;



        display version information and terminate





    &opt_q;
    &opt_quiet;



        do not display warning messages





    &opt_v;
    &opt_verbose;



        display concise intermediate messages





    &opt_f;
    &opt_formats;



       list accepted formats





    &opt_i;
    &opt_in;=&format;


use &format; format as the input format




    &opt_o;
    &opt_out;=&format;


use &format; format as the output format




    &opt_l;
    &opt_lpe;=&file;


use &file; as the LPE from which the input LTS was
        generated; this is needed to store the correct parameter
	names of states when saving in &fsm; format and to convert non-mCRL2
	LTSs to a mCRL2 LTS





    &opt_n;
    &opt_no_state;


leave out state information when saving in ˙ format





  The following options are relevant for LTS minimisation only.



    &opt_none;


do not minimise the LTS (this is the default)





    &opt_s;
    &opt_strong;


minimise using strong bisimulation





    &opt_b;
    &opt_branching;


minimise using branching bisimulation





    &opt_a;
    &opt_add;


do not minimise but save a copy of the original LTS extended with a
      state parameter indicating the bisimulation class a state belongs to.
      This means that every state is extended with a number in such a way that
      (only) equivalent states have the same number. (This option only works
      for mCRL2 LTSs)





    &opt_tau;=&actnames;


consider actions with a name in the comma separated list &actnames;
      to be a internal (tau) actions in addition to those defined as such by
      the input. This means that before minimisation all specified actions are
      first replaced by tau actions. In the case &opt_add; is used, these tau
      actions will only used internally to compute the equivalence classes; the
      output will have the original actions.
